ec\/speed 3<b>. Fill chilled tarts with filling, garnish with reserved nuts and bake for 20-25 minutes (350°F). Allow to cool 5 minutes and while still hot brush tops with jelly. Cool completely before removing from tart pans. Serve immediately or store in an airtight container."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Dough should not be overworked. If dough becomes soft, place it in the refrigerator (approx. 15 min.) until it can be handled easily again.","Replace tart pans with a 12-hole cupcake pan. Grease generously with butter. Divide dough and roll out 12 circles (3¼ in.). Place pastry into each cupcake hole and press into shape. After tarts cool, run a small knife around edges of tarts to loosen for easy removal.","Place tarts back in the oven for 5 minutes to caramelize and set the jelly.","Replace pecan halves with pecan pieces.","Orange zest can be added to filling to intensify the flavor."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h 30m","2h 25m","20 pieces"]}